USAGE

Code Beautifier for C/C++/Java        Version 2.1n Aug 14, 1997

Usage: cbVan input.fil [indent] [tab]
(Executing:  E:\HBC\CBV\UP21\CBVANW95.EXE)

input.fil - input source file in current directory
          - enclose long file name with space in double quotes
indent    - where 'indent' is a number from 1 to 8 equal
            to number of spaces for each indent level
            Default 4 if not supplied on cmd line
tab       - output tabs when 't' is supplied on the cmd line

EXAMPLES:
- cbVan hello.c
- cbVan hello.cpp 6
- cbVan hello.java 8 t
- cbVan "hello world.cxx"

NOTES:
- at normal end-of-processing, original source is in input.bak
- if abnormal end, original source is not changed


